        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-226",
        "content": "Over the first half crown he had said to himself: \"Milk and new laid eggs.\" Now, as he pocketed the second, he added the other two things mentioned by the parish doctor: \"Soup and jelly\"; and his heart glowed.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-slow_e-normal",
